Bussiness.description: Discover the extraordinary heritage and culture of Cayman through this lovingly restored window into the 18th century that's just a 20-minute drive from George Town. At a moment in the Cayman Islands when most people inhabited small, thatch-covered homes, a wealthy Englishman, utilizing slave labor from Jamaica, built an impressive 3-storey building called Pedro St. James.
